Update PlatformProvider with new features and condition checks
Included the use of the ShopCustomer model in the PlatformProvider file to enhance functionality. Added new badges to the navbar, and provided additional condition checks for the visibility of menu items based on certain business rules.-

Revise data retrieval and filtering in CustomerEditScreen and ShopOrders
The data retrieval attribute 'orders' has been renamed to 'shop_orders' in CustomerEditScreen, to avoid confusion. In the ShopOrders model, 'customer_id' was added to the allowable filters and sorts in order to streamline data access and improve searchability.

Update voucher balance attribute in DeviceController
The 'amount' attribute of the voucher in the DeviceController has been refactored to 'money'. This change will show the monetary value of the voucher balance, improving data accuracy and consistency.

Update voucher balance attribute in DeviceController
The 'amount' attribute of the voucher in the DeviceController has been refactored to 'money'. This change will show the monetary value of the voucher balance, improving data accuracy and consistency.

Refactor CheckBox behavior in shop settings
The CheckBoxes in the ShopSettings and ShopVoucherEdit files now use sendTrueOrFalse() method to send Boolean values to the back-end. Earlier, string values "on" or null were sent, leading to inaccurate or inconsistent results. Now, the CheckBoxes will directly send either True or False, enhancing data precision and code maintainability.
